          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Of authors. In the pile neutron spectrum the (n,gamma)",
                "CS is much greater than",
                " (n,p) (energy release 0.147+-0.01MeV),",
                " (n,alpha) (energy release 9.23+-0.02 MeV),",
                " (n,2n) (threshold 7.2+0.1MeV) CSs,",
                "  (n,p) and (n,alpha) CS were estimated at 3MeV energy",
                " to be of order 3*10**-7 b,",
                "so measured absorption CS is almost identical to",
                " (n,gamma) CS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " For scattering - negligible.",
                " For \"slowing down\" - measured by heavy water- +0.7 mb",
                " in measured CS.",
                " For allowance of displacement of air by sample at",
                " moving in the center of pile, nitrogen CS was used,",
                " correction 2.6 mb.",
                "For impurities contribution - 6.9+2.4-0.8 mb,",
                "rewritten as 7.7+-1.6 mb."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Raw value of CS obtained in measurement with other",
                "sample(lent by B.B.Kinsey Atomic Energy of Canada,Ltd.)",
                " is 34.3 mb (no corrections applied)."
              ]
            }
